I finally asked these dentists who they would recommend to find out exactly what was wrong.
The answer was unanimous, Dr. De Andrade is your guy.
I called that day an was seen that day.
The 4th dentist of the day I might add.
I've had a lot of dental work done and this was by far the most professional and FUN office I have ever been in.
Dr. De Andrade showed me on his High Def Big Screen exactly why I was having a problem.
The bone graft on one side didn't take.
It was obvious to see on his giant screen but missed by 5 other dentists and surgeons.
They scheduled the surgery to remove the implant and redo the bone graft the next morning.
An hour later I was on my way.
I have had no pain whatsover.
I haven't even had an Advil.
This man is a true specialist.
The other dentists couldn't even remove the crown on the implant.
They all said they had to cut it off.
Thats because they dont have the tools for all the different implants.
Dr. D has them all and had the crown off in 5 minutes even though the screw was stripped from everybody else trying to remove it with the wrong tool.
Save yourself a lot of grief.
Go see Dr. De Andrade.
Learn from my mistake.Get the job done by someone that actually specializes in this field!!

